ce:section.ce:para:
After exploring the sensitivity and selectivity of TEF-CDs with respect to chlorpyrifos and quinalphos, the practicality of TEF-CDs was assessed for the determination of quinalphos and chlorpyrifos in spiked fruits (apple, strawberry, and lemon) and rice samples, where the content of quinalphos and chlorpyrifos is frequently noticed. The collected fruits and rice samples were obtained from a nearby marketplace in Surat, Gujarat, India. Meanwhile, the fruits and rice samples were prepared separately using the above-mentioned procedure and treated with different concentrations of chlorpyrifos (0.05, 0.1, and 0.5 μM) and quinalphos (0.01, 0.05, and 0.1 μM), which the amounts of chlorpyrifos and quinalphos were estimated by the aforesaid procedure. The recovery ranges of quinalphos were found to range from 99.68 to 99.80% for the rice sample and 97.50–99.62% for the fruit sample, with the relative standard deviation (RSD) being in the range of 1.4–11.2% (Table 3
                        ). Additionally, the recovery ranges of chlorpyrifos were found to range from 98.29 to 99.40% for the rice sample and 96.32–99.49% for the fruit sample, with the relative standard deviation (RSD) ranging from 0.1 to 12.6% (Table 4
                        ). These results demonstrated that the TEF-CDs-fluorescence method could be applied to detect chlorpyrifos and quinalphos in the fruits and rice samples.
